### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/releated to the feature request?

forms

### Description

With Typed Forms on it's way to framework and RFC https://github.com/angular/angular/discussions/44513 I have a proposition to upgrade current implementation of FormArray. 

Lets say we have a simple form array:
```
type PhoneNumberType = 'Mobile' | 'Work';
interface PhoneNumbers {
  phoneNumber: string;
  type: PhoneNumberType
};

const formArray = new FormArray<PhoneNumbers >([]);
```

Now to patch this form array we need to with this data:
```
const dataFromServer: PhoneNumbers [] = [
  {type: 'Mobile', phoneNumber: '123456789'}, 
  {type: 'Work', phoneNumber: '123456780'}
]
```
we need to:
```
//clear the form array to make sure there is no controls
formArray.clear()
//iterate through data and push new form controls
for (phoneNumber of dataFromServer) {
  formArray.push(createPhoneNumberFormGroup(phoneNumber ))
}
```

This seem straightforward until we go deeper and have more nested forms like:
```
interface ContactDetailsForm {
 phoneNumber: FormArray<PhoneNumbers>;
 webContacts: FormArray<WebContact>;
}

interface ComanyBranchDetailsForm {
 name: string;
 addresses: FormGroup<ContactAddressForm>;
 contactDetails: FormArray<ContactDetailsForm>;
}

const formArray = new FormArray<ComanyBranchDetailsForm>([]);
```

now if we want to patch it with data we would need to do the same as before but on every level so 
```
//inside a component/service
public formArray = new FormArray<ComanyBranchDetailsForm>([]);

// ...
// ...

patchForm(data: ComanyBranchDetails[]) {
// this is naive aproach, we always clear form arrays and make them for scratch. That's only one possible strategy, other could try to reuse already present controls etc.
// I am aware that this could be aproached in few ways

  // we cannot simply do 
  // this.formArray.setValue(data) 
 // because we don't have form groups in form arrays so again

 this.formArray.clear()
 for (companyBranchData of data) {
  formArray.push(createCompanyBranchDetailsFormGroup(companyBranchData )) 
 }
}

createCompanyBranchDetailsFormGroup(companyBranchData: ComanyBranchDetails) {
const contactDetailsFromArray = new FormArray<ContactDetailsForm>([]);

 for (contactDetail of companyBranchData.contactDetails) {
  contactDetailsFromArray .push(createContactDetailFormGroup(contactDetail )) 
 }

const addressesFromArray = new FormArray<ContactAddressForm>([]);

 for (address of companyBranchData.addresses) {
  addressesFromArray .push(createContactAddressFormGroup(address )) 
 }

const formGroup = new FormGroup<ComanyBranchDetailsForm>({
  name: new FormControl(companyBranchData.name);
  addresses: addressesFromArray ;
  contactDetails: contactDetailsFromArray ;
 });
}

createContactDetailFormGroup(contactDetails: ContactDetails) {
//again this is have 2 form arrays so we would need to create those again etc.
}

```
as you see something that simple as filling form with data which is super simple for forms with no  form arrays
```
const form = new FormGroup({
a: new FormGroup({a1: new FormControl(), a2: new FormControl())), 
b: new FormGroup({b1: new FormControl(), b2: new FormControl())), 
})

form.setValue({a: {a1: 'a1 value', a2: 'a2 value}, b: {b1: 'b1 value', b2: 'b2 value} )
```
becomes the above.

What's more with typed forms also comes in default value, which is impossible to implement for `FormArray` as I understands.



### Proposed solution


The proposition is quite simple:

// current constructor
```
constructor(controls: CtrlT, validatorOrOpts?: ValidatorFn | ValidatorFn[] | AbstractControlOptions | null, asyncValidator?: AsyncValidatorFn | AsyncValidatorFn[] | null);
```

//proposed addition
```
type InitiasisationStrategy = 'AlwaysCreate' | 'Reuse' | 'None' ;
type ClearStrategy = 'Leave' | 'Delete';

type FormArrayControlOptions  = AbstractControlOptions  & {
 initialiser?:  (data: any) => CtrlT;
 initiasisationStrategy?: InitiasisationStrategy;
 clearStrategy?: ClearStrategy;
}
```

```
constructor(controls: CtrlT, validatorOrOpts?: ValidatorFn | ValidatorFn[] | FormArrayControlOptions  | null, asyncValidator?: AsyncValidatorFn | AsyncValidatorFn[] | null);
```

Now to patch this form array we need to with this data:
```
const dataFromServer: PhoneNumber [] = [
  {type: 'Mobile', phoneNumber: '123456789'}, 
  {type: 'Work', phoneNumber: '123456780'}
]

const formArray = new FormArray<PhoneNumbers>(dataFromServer, {
  initiasisationStrategy: 'AlwaysCreate',
  initialiser: (data:  PhoneNumber) => new FormGroup<PhoneNumber>(data), ‚Äã
});

// Now we can also later update it with ease

formArray.setValue([[
  {type: 'Mobile', phoneNumber: '123456789'}, 
  {type: 'Work', phoneNumber: '123456782'},  //modyfing 
  {type: 'Work', phoneNumber: '123456780'}, // adding
]]);
```
Again this would make bigger change in the second more complicated example.

As for what `InitiasisationStrategy` stands for would be:
`AlwaysCreate` - always create new form groups//controls using initialiser
`Reuse` - if present at the given index the reuse the control using setValue/patchValue accordingly
`None` or `undefined` - current implementation


Similar `ClearStrategy`
`Leave`  or `undefined`- Leaves group/control if new value does not contains  value for given index //present implementation 
'Delete` - Delete all controls at unused indexes // only applied to on setValue


### Alternatives considered

There is no real alternatives other that to use what is already given.

This is a very rough and quickly written issue - if given some feedback it could be improved for sure. 
Of course there would be many things that would need to be checked, but this change should be possible to be implemented without many braking changes apart from interface changes;


### FormTouple
As for possibly incoming Form Touple I don't see use for this implementation as `FormTouple` would be used for mixing data of diffrent types and would be of fixed size anyway (and possible fixed controls ?);

### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/releated to the feature request?

